       for i in range(n):\n            if i % 2 == 0:\n                # For even index, compare with neighbors\n                left = nums[i - 1] if i > 0 else float('inf')\n                right = nums[i + 1] if i < n - 1 else float('inf')\n                target = min(left, right) - 1\n                if nums[i] > target:\n                    moves_even += nums[i] - target\n            else:\n                # For odd index, compare with neighbors\n                left = nums[i - 1] if i > 0 else float('inf')\n                right = nums[i + 1] if i < n - 1 else float('inf')\n                target = min(left, right) - 1\n                if nums[i] > target:\n                    moves_odd += nums[i] - target\n        \n        return min(moves_even, moves_odd)\n```\n\nThis solution calculates the minimum number of moves required to make the array a zigzag array by considering two scenarios: making even-indexed elements greater than their neighbors and making odd-indexed elements greater than their neighbors. It then returns the minimum of the two scenarios.", "estimated_date": 1564876800000}